16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
18 Resources Board from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
19 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
20 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
21 of Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000.00) for the purpose of providing
22 water infrastructure funding to a rural water sewer and solid waste
23 management district in the central region of the state experiencing
24
Req. No. 2140 Page 1
1 priv ate water well contamination from an unknown source and needing
2 connected with a public water supply.
3 SECTION 2. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
4 Resources Board from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
5 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
6 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
7 of Two Million Dollars ($2,000,000.00) for the purpose of
8 constructing water lines in a county with a population greater than
9 one hundred fifty thousand (150,000) and less than two hundred
10 thousand (200,000) according to the latest Federal Decennial Census
11 and located in a community not adjacent to a major roadway
12 designated as an interstate.
13 SECTION 3. There is hereby appropriated to the Oklahoma Water
14 Resources Board from any monies not otherwise appropriated from the
15 Progressing Rural Economic Prosperity Fund of the State Treasury
16 created in Section 256 of Title 62 of the Oklahoma Statutes, the sum
17 of Two Hundred Thousand Dollars ($200,000.00) for the purpose of
18 establishing grant programs that facilitate the design,
19 construction, and maintenance of water and wastewater
20 infrastructure, and to improve the condition of publicly owned,
21 deficient dams regulated by the Oklahoma Water Resources Board.
22 SECTION 4. This act shall become effective July 1, 2025.
23 SECTION 5. It being immediately necessary for the preservation
24 of the public peace, health or safety, an emergency is hereby
